24 forum for legislators in Arkansas, Texas, Louisiana, Oklahoma, and New Mexico
25 to learn about and collaborate on energy policy and issues relevant to their
26 constituents; and
27
28 WHEREAS, the Energy Council has expanded to include fourteen (14)
29 member states and the Canadian provinces of Alberta and Saskatchewan that
30 actively participate in the development of state and federal energy and
31 environmental policy; and
32
33 WHEREAS, the Energy Council helps to inform lawmakers about economic
34 markets and emerging technology and practices relating to an evolving energy
35 landscape; and
